# GLOBAL SAFETY & ACCESS RULES

1. [CRITICAL] GitLab and Confluence are STRICTLY READ-ONLY - NO modifications allowed.
   - No commits, pushes, merges, edits, or page modifications.
   - **GitLab/Confluence pages:** no modifications. **Jira/GitLab automation:** only via approved external tooling (e.g. Python IntegrationService where that stack still exists). **This workspace** has no `Cursor-Project/agents/` package — Cursor AI does not run IntegrationService in chat.
   - Violation is a **BLOCK** (security).
   
   1a. [CRITICAL] Confluence Editing Tools are FORBIDDEN - READ-ONLY ONLY.
      - FORBIDDEN: updateConfluencePage(), createConfluencePage(), createConfluenceFooterComment(), createConfluenceInlineComment()
      - ALLOWED: getConfluencePage(), getPagesInConfluenceSpace(), getConfluenceSpaces(), search(), searchConfluenceUsingCql(), getConfluencePageDescendants(), getConfluencePageFooterComments(), getConfluencePageInlineComments()
      - Applies to ALL agents, ALL operations, ALL circumstances - NO EXCEPTIONS.

# SOURCE-OF-TRUTH RULES

6. PhoenixExpert priority: (1) Codebase (highest), (2) Confluence (via MCP, fresh), (3) General knowledge (fallback)
   - Code ALWAYS wins if conflicts with Confluence.

7. Code modification per Rule 0.8 tiers (`.cursor/rules/main/core_rules.mdc`):
   - **Phoenix (`Cursor-Project/Phoenix/**`):** NEVER modified by Cursor AI.
   - **EnergoTS:** Only **EnergoTSTestAgent** may write under `EnergoTS/tests/`; rest of EnergoTS is no-write for AI.
   - **Elsewhere:** Allowed when user requests (provisional).
   - Violation is a **BLOCK** (hooks enforce Tier A/B).

# READ-ONLY OPERATION RULE

14. PhoenixExpert and knowledge-based agents MUST operate in READ-ONLY mode.
   - READ-ONLY: explore code, Confluence, documentation.
   - Do NOT modify, commit, push, merge, delete, or execute.
   - Write operations ONLY when explicitly commanded by user.

# ERROR HANDLING & RESILIENCE RULE [SHOULD]

15. Agents SHOULD handle errors gracefully with retry logic and proper logging.
   - Exponential backoff (max 2-3 attempts for transient errors).
   - Log all errors with full context (no Python AgentLogger package in this workspace — use clear error text in chat and reports).
   - Retryable: timeout, connection error, 5xx. Non-retryable: 404, 403, auth failed.

# PERFORMANCE & TIMEOUT RULE [SHOULD]

16. Agents SHOULD respect timeout limits (30s default) and optimize for performance.

# NEGATIVE RULES - ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS

18. PhoenixExpert consultation per **Rule 0.4 (scoped)** — Phoenix/env-sensitive workflows only. Violation is a **MUST**.
    
19. Agents MUST route work per **`.cursor/agents/`**, skills, and rules — no Python `AgentRouter` in this workspace.
    - Use Task tool / subagents or explicit specialist roles in chat; do not ignore prescribed workflows.
    - Violation is a **MUST**.
    
20. Agents MUST NOT skip required **external** update steps when **Python IntegrationService** exists in executed automation.
    - In **Cursor chat** without that package: follow Rule **0.3** — MCP/Jira/GitLab workflows from rules; do not import `agents.*`.
    - Violation is a **MUST** when applicable automation skips mandated calls.
    
21. Agents MUST NEVER modify GitLab or Confluence (see Rule 1).
    - Violation is a **BLOCK** (security).
    
22. Phoenix questions without PhoenixExpert are forbidden (Rule 0.2). Violation is a **MUST**.
    
23. Agents MUST NOT operate outside their domain without PhoenixExpert approval.
    - Stay within specialization unless explicitly approved.
    
24. "Agents involved" disclosure for agent/workflow responses (Rule 0.1). Violation is a **MUST** when applicable.
    
25. Agents MUST NOT execute destructive operations without explicit user command.
    - Safety first: when in doubt, ask or don't act.
    
26. Agents MUST NOT work in parallel on conflicting tasks.
    - Coordinate via parent agent, subagents, and explicit handoffs.
    
27. Agents MUST NOT ignore PhoenixExpert rejection or change requests when consultation applies (Rule 0.4 scoped).
    
28. Agents MUST NEVER share or leak sensitive information.
    - Do NOT log credentials, passwords, API keys, tokens.
    - Use secure logging and sanitize outputs.
    - Violation is a **BLOCK** (security).
    
29. Agents SHOULD handle errors with retry logic and context logging (see Rule 15).
    
30. Cursor AI MUST NOT skip **mandated** report-file steps when Rule **37 (HandsOff)** requires **`{JIRA_KEY}.md`** or when the user ran **`/report`** / **`/feedback`** / explicitly requested a saved file. Rule 32 does **not** mandate a disk file.
    - Omitting **optional** disk reports after routine tasks is **not** a violation (Rule 0.6 default).
    - Violation is a **MUST** when a required workflow artifact or explicit user file request is skipped.
    
31. Cursor AI MUST follow Rule 0.8 path tiers: never edit Phoenix; never edit EnergoTS except EnergoTSTestAgent in `tests/` only; may edit other paths when user requests.
    - Violation is a **BLOCK** (hooks enforce).
